  "body": "Base image brings some vulnerabilities that need to be patched.\r\n\r\n```\r\ndocker scan --severity high sigp/lighthouse:v2.1.4                       \r\n\r\nTesting sigp/lighthouse:v2.1.4...\r\n\r\n✗ High severity vulnerability found in openssl/libssl1.1\r\n  Description: CVE-2022-0778\r\n  Info: https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-UBUNTU2004-OPENSSL-2426343\r\n  Introduced through: openssl/libssl-dev@1.1.1f-1ubuntu2.11, ca-certificates@20210119~20.04.2\r\n  From: openssl/libssl-dev@1.1.1f-1ubuntu2.11 > openssl/libssl1.1@1.1.1f-1ubuntu2.11\r\n  From: ca-certificates@20210119~20.04.2 > openssl@1.1.1f-1ubuntu2.11 > openssl/libssl1.1@1.1.1f-1ubuntu2.11\r\n  From: ca-certificates@20210119~20.04.2 > openssl@1.1.1f-1ubuntu2.11\r\n  and 1 more...\r\n  Image layer: 'apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends libssl-dev ca-certificates'\r\n  Fixed in: 1.1.1f-1ubuntu2.12\r\n\r\n\r\nOrganization:      \r\nPackage manager:   deb\r\nProject name:      docker-image|sigp/lighthouse\r\nDocker image:      sigp/lighthouse:v2.1.4\r\nPlatform:          linux/amd64\r\nBase image:        ubuntu:20.04\r\nLicenses:          enabled\r\n\r\nTested 97 dependencies for known issues, found 1 issue.\r\n\r\nBase Image    Vulnerabilities  Severity\r\nubuntu:20.04  15               0 critical, 0 high, 1 medium, 14 low\r\n\r\nRecommendations for base image upgrade:\r\n\r\nMajor upgrades\r\nBase Image     Vulnerabilities  Severity\r\nubuntu:impish  13               0 critical, 0 high, 1 medium, 12 low\r\n```",
